table_fun <- function(data) {   
  data %>% gt() %>% 
  tab_style(
    style = cell_borders(
      sides = c("left", "right"),
      color = "grey"),
    locations = list(
      cells_body(
      columns = everything()
      ),
      cells_column_labels()
    )
    )
}

Preface

This document describes and summarizes the various values that are used by Spectran. Because the tables are comprehensive, it makes little sense to go through them sequentially. Instead, you can use the table of contents to jump to the section of interest.

Action Spectra

The units in the following tables are nm (nanometers) for wavelength, and 1 for the action spectrum. The action spectrum is a relative measure, and therefore has no unit. The data for alpha-opic action spectra were taken from the CIE S026 Toolbox. The 2° photopic luminous efficiency function V(λ) (between 380-780 nm) was taken from the ISO/CIE 23539:2023.
